article.headline: North Texas 93, Belhaven 66
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Calvin Watson scored 23 points and North Texas pulled away in the second half to beat Belhaven 93-66 on Thursday night. The teams battled close in the first half, with North Texas (10-3) taking a 37-35 lead into the break. But the Mean Green stepped up their shooting, improving from 38 percent in the first half to 56 percent in the second. Quincy Williams added 20 points on 9-for-12 shooting for the Mean Green. Watson and Williams led the team with eight rebounds apiece. Watson made all six of his free throws. Bobby Johnson led Belhaven (7-5) with 28 points. He shot 11-of-16 from the field, including both of his 3-point attempts. Dax Miller added 12 points and five assists. Daniel Sturgis led the Blazers with six rebounds. North Texas took its biggest lead, a 27-point-margin, with 1:20 to play. North Texas shot 47 percent for the game to 44 percent for Belhaven.
